Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,DCMain,,0000,0000,0000,,Detective Conan Episode 1001 "The Moonlight Sonata Murder (Part Two)"
Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.52,0:00:03.48,Office,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(460,1)}Moonshade Island Village Office
Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.90,0:00:03.48,DCMain,NARUMI,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Based on that,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.61,0:00:09.98,DCMain,NARUMI,0000,0000,0000,,I believe only a few minutes have passed \Nsince the victim Mayor Kuroiwa's death.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.15,0:00:13.61,Narumi,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,460)}Asai Narumi (26)\NDoctor
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.16,0:00:11.93,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}A-A few minutes?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.93,0:00:12.78,DCMain,NARUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.78,0:00:15.16,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}That seems correct.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.62,0:00:20.27,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,There's only five and a half minutes of \Nsilence at the beginning of this tape
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.27,0:00:23.00,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,of the "Moonlight Sonata"'s second movement.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.31,0:00:24.48,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.98,0:00:25.74,DCMain,POLICE,0000,0000,0000,,Inspector.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.36,0:00:30.25,DCMain,POLICE,0000,0000,0000,,There's a musical score written in blood \Nbeneath the chair the victim was sitting in.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.25,0:00:31.26,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.56,0:00:37.09,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,More musical scores.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.09,0:00:40.73,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Could this also be a dying \Nmessage left by the victim?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.73,0:00:41.73,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.93,0:00:48.60,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,If he had the time and strength to write all this \Nwith his own blood, he would've called for help.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.60,0:00:49.61,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Stay out of this!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.18,0:00:55.15,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,You idiot! That's valuable evidence!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.68,0:00:59.88,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,It's okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.60,0:01:03.28,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,A journey of a thousand miles \Nstarts with the first step!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.28,0:01:05.12,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Solve 1,000 mysteries and enter a new world!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.48,0:01:07.45,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The sound of a piano rings \Nout across a remote island!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.45,0:01:09.71,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,What conclusion will it pass down?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.71,0:01:11.34,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Always determining the one truth
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.34,0:01:13.06,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,with the body of a child \Nand the mind of an adult,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.06,0:01:15.64,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,his name is Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.03,0:03:03.03,DCEpTitle,EPTITLE,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(397,1)}The "Moonlight Sonata" Murder \N(Part Two)
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.60,0:03:01.52,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,"The 'Moonlight Sonata' Murder, Part Two!"
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.60,0:03:06.04,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Let's jump right into it, Nishimoto-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.24,0:03:10.66,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,You're the person who \Ndiscovered Kuroiwa-san's body.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.08,0:03:14.59,Ken,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,460)}Nishimoto Ken (55)\NUnemployed
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.51,0:03:15.54,DCMain,NISHIMOTO,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Kuroiwa told me to meet him \Nin the broadcast room at 6:30.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.81,0:03:21.32,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Kuroiwa-san did say he was \Nmeeting someone this evening.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.32,0:03:23.68,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Are you sure you didn't tell him to meet \Nyou there so you could kill him?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.68,0:03:24.68,DCMain,NISHIMOTO,0000,0000,0000,,O-Of course not!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.97,0:03:27.26,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Then why did he want to meet you?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.02,0:03:29.24,DCMain,NISHIMOTO,0000,0000,0000,,I...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.39,0:03:32.65,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like I'm right.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.21,0:03:34.24,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,The culprit is—
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.24,0:03:35.44,DCMain,REIKO,0000,0000,0000,,It's Shimizu!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.44,0:03:38.86,DCMain,REIKO,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}With mayoral election candidates \NKawashima and my dad out of the way,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.65,0:03:39.07,Reiko,RIGHT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,460)}Kuroiwa Reiko (27)\NKuroiwa's Only Daughter
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.65,0:03:39.07,Shuichi,LEFT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,460)}Murasawa Shuichi (27)\NReiko's Fiancé
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.86,0:03:42.86,DCMain,REIKO,0000,0000,0000,,the mayor's seat automatically becomes his!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.86,0:03:43.82,DCMain,SHIMIZU,0000,0000,0000,,Don't be ridiculous!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.86,0:03:46.33,Kazuaki - Copy,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,460)}Shimizu Masato (49)\NMayoral Election Candidate
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.13,0:03:48.64,DCMain,SHIMIZU,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}There's no way I'd kill two \Npeople just to become the mayor!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.31,0:03:49.32,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,What are you looking at, Conan-kun?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.32,0:03:51.33,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,This musical score left at the crime scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.86,0:03:56.13,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I think this is probably a coded \Nmessage left by the culprit.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.64,0:04:00.13,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Do these sharps and flats mean anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.32,0:04:02.75,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,They refer to the black keys on the piano.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.75,0:04:03.51,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.51,0:04:06.99,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,You know, because they're symbols \Nfor a half step up or down.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.11,0:04:10.31,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The keys...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.14,0:04:14.49,DCMain,REIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry up and catch the murderer, Inspector!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.49,0:04:15.49,DCMain,REIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Otherwise, more people will die!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.49,0:04:19.15,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,You know you're next.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.94,0:04:19.15,Kazuaki,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,1)}Hirata Kazuaki (31)\NSecretary to the Mayor
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.44,0:04:20.79,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Conan-kun?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.79,0:04:23.65,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Once you figure out the \Nkey to this code, it's simple.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.18,0:04:28.92,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,They've assigned the letters of the alphabet to \Nthe keys of the piano in order from left to right
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.92,0:04:33.66,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,and written the corresponding \Nsounds as a musical score.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.03,0:04:38.92,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Reading the sheet music left at Kawashima-san's \Nmurder according to that assumption, we get...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.24,0:04:43.67,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,"You know you're next."
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.06,0:04:44.71,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,See?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.71,0:04:46.27,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Wow!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.27,0:04:49.10,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Th-Then what about the \Nmusical score written in blood?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.57,0:04:50.47,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Let's see.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.21,0:04:56.13,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,"The hellfire's grudge is settled."
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.13,0:04:58.73,DCMain,SHIMIZU,0000,0000,0000,,Th-The hellfire's grudge? Could it be?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.12,0:05:02.65,DCMain,REIKO,0000,0000,0000,,The pianist who burned \Nhimself to death 12 years ago?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.17,0:05:03.99,DCMain,NISHIMOTO,0000,0000,0000,,It's him.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.56,0:05:09.12,DCMain,NISHIMOTO,0000,0000,0000,,I knew it. He's alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.64,0:05:11.63,DCMain,NISHIMOTO,0000,0000,0000,,Aso Keiji is alive!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.63,0:05:13.41,DCMain,POLICE,0000,0000,0000,,He's not alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.76,0:05:17.54,DCMain,POLICE,0000,0000,0000,,The corpse found in the ruins \Nmatched his dental records.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.54,0:05:19.04,DCMain,POLICE,0000,0000,0000,,That was definitely him.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.25,0:05:21.72,DCMain,POLICE,0000,0000,0000,,Everything burnt to the ground.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.72,0:05:25.67,DCMain,POLICE,0000,0000,0000,,All that was left was the sheet \Nmusic inside his fireproof safe.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.78,0:05:27.05,DCMain,BOTH,0000,0000,0000,,Sh-Sheet music?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.16,0:05:30.09,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Where is that sheet music now?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.09,0:05:32.63,DCMain,POLICE,0000,0000,0000,,In the community center's safe.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.63,0:05:34.72,DCMain,POLICE,0000,0000,0000,,I believe I have the keys at the substation.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.72,0:05:36.81,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Then hurry up and bring them here!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.14,0:05:38.94,DCMain,POLICE,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.94,0:05:40.69,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I'll go with you!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.77,0:05:46.32,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, did Aso-san really set \Nhis own house on fire?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.32,0:05:48.95,DCMain,POLICE,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, according to the witnesses.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.40,0:05:50.83,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,What witnesses?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.40,0:05:55.02,DCMain,POLICE,0000,0000,0000,,The previous mayor \NKameyama-san, Kawashima-san,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.02,0:05:58.96,DCMain,POLICE,0000,0000,0000,,the current mayor Kuroiwa, and Nishimoto-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.96,0:05:59.33,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.84,0:06:02.84,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Aside from Nishimoto-san, they're all dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.10,0:06:05.17,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Then what about that Murasawa guy?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.32,0:06:09.80,DCMain,POLICE,0000,0000,0000,,He came to this island about three years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.80,0:06:13.18,DCMain,POLICE,0000,0000,0000,,He got engaged to the mayor's \Ndaughter just the other day.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.52,0:06:17.08,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Really? What about the mayor's \Nsecretary Hirata-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.08,0:06:19.46,DCMain,POLICE,0000,0000,0000,,He's a strange fellow.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.46,0:06:21.56,DCMain,POLICE,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know what he was doing,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.72,0:06:25.57,DCMain,POLICE,0000,0000,0000,,but I often saw him secretly meeting with \NKawashima-san at the community center.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.72,0:06:27.81,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,What about Shimizu-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.81,0:06:29.81,DCMain,POLICE,0000,0000,0000,,He's a respectable man.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.81,0:06:32.95,DCMain,POLICE,0000,0000,0000,,His only flaw is that he's a bit short-tempered.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.25,0:06:38.37,DCMain,POLICE,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? That's odd.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.61,0:06:41.38,DCMain,POLICE,0000,0000,0000,,I know I put it around here somewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.38,0:06:44.63,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Jeez. We've been looking \Nfor over an hour already.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.85,0:06:47.51,DCMain,POLICE,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, here it is. This is the key.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.70,0:06:49.76,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Then let's hurry back to Inspector Megure.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.76,0:06:50.34,DCMain,POLICE,0000,0000,0000,,Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.34,0:06:51.61,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,You're too late.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.61,0:06:52.01,DCMain,BOTH,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.31,0:06:55.73,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone got tired of waiting and left.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.73,0:06:56.14,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.46,0:06:58.14,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,They let the suspects leave, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.24,0:07:04.90,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. Since the culprit's last message \Nsaid, "The hellfire's grudge is settled,"
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.27,0:07:07.90,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,they thought there wouldn't \Nbe anymore murders.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.90,0:07:08.95,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,That can't be!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.95,0:07:11.91,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,There's still the third movement \Nof the "Moonlight Sonata."
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.28,0:07:14.24,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to the community center!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.24,0:07:15.91,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, Conan-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.39,0:07:18.16,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Officer, hurry.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.47,0:07:20.96,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,We need to check that sheet \Nmusic as soon as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.96,0:07:22.67,DCMain,POLICE,0000,0000,0000,,Don't rush me.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.27,0:07:31.04,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, did you just hear a strange noise \Ncoming from the room with the piano?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.48,0:07:32.53,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Did you?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.60,0:07:39.85,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Bastard!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.12,0:07:47.28,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Murasawa-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.97,0:07:48.78,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Ran?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.60,0:07:51.74,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Ran-neechan!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.59,0:07:53.51,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.90,0:07:58.16,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Nishimoto-san...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.91,0:08:01.77,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Officer, contact the Inspector immediately!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.77,0:08:03.30,DCMain,POLICE,0000,0000,0000,,Got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.63,0:08:07.72,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,That was the sound of this stopping.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.46,0:08:10.60,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,It contains a 60 minute tape.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.60,0:08:15.94,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Since each side is 30 minutes, Nishimoto-san \Nprobably died within the last 30 minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.75,0:08:17.88,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Conan-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.49,0:08:20.35,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Look next to Nishimoto-san's feet.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.35,0:08:20.85,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.17,0:08:23.31,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Sheet music.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.18,0:08:27.31,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,What does it say this time?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.13,0:08:29.11,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,"Suicide note."
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.08,0:08:34.27,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Suicide note? You mean Nishimoto-san...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.90,0:08:36.70,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,He killed himself, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.06,0:08:42.67,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,According to this note, he regretted \Nkilling Kawashima and Kuroiwa.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.67,0:08:45.28,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,So it was Nishimoto who killed them.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.08,0:08:50.71,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,His motive was that he \Ndidn't want the mistake
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.71,0:08:53.25,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,he committed with Kawashima, \NKuroiwa, Kameyama,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.25,0:08:58.27,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,who died two years ago, and Aso,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.27,0:09:00.51,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,who killed himself 12 years ago, to be exposed.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.77,0:09:03.18,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Even the pianist Aso?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.18,0:09:04.31,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.31,0:09:08.27,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,It says that Aso came up with the code.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.27,0:09:12.62,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,They must've done something using this code.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.62,0:09:13.99,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.99,0:09:19.53,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Nishimoto believed the sheet music that \Nsurvived the fire described their old secret.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.53,0:09:23.66,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,In order to destroy the sheet \Nmusic, he broke into the safe,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.99,0:09:27.89,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,but couldn't find the sheet \Nmusic, so he killed himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.89,0:09:28.60,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.60,0:09:30.24,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I don't think he killed himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.24,0:09:30.75,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.00,0:09:34.51,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Look closely at the spot \Nwhere the body's feet were.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.75,0:09:37.26,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,There's nothing there for him to step on.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.59,0:09:40.98,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Normally a person wouldn't be able to \Ndo that without a step of some kind.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.98,0:09:44.52,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, it's hard to \Nimagine that this was a suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.81,0:09:46.77,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I saw someone suspicious.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.03,0:09:47.88,DCMain,BOTH,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.88,0:09:49.90,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,There were two people in the piano room.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.29,0:09:55.50,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,One of them broke the window and fled, \Nbut the other one was Murasawa.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.50,0:09:57.90,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,He was on the floor because \Nsomeone struck him.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.90,0:10:00.91,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Doctor Narumi's examining him \Nin the piano room right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.26,0:10:02.92,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,You should've told us that sooner.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.54,0:10:11.86,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Officer, did you find Aso-san's sheet music?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.86,0:10:12.38,DCMain,POLICE,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.78,0:10:15.71,DCMain,POLICE,0000,0000,0000,,After all, it happened 12 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.07,0:10:18.63,DCMain,POLICE,0000,0000,0000,,I have no idea where I put it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.90,0:10:22.52,DCMain,NARUMI,0000,0000,0000,,I believe he has a concussion,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.52,0:10:25.08,DCMain,NARUMI,0000,0000,0000,,but I can't say for certain unless I \Nexamine him properly at the clinic.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.08,0:10:26.59,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.59,0:10:30.50,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,By the way, Kuroiwa-san, what \Nwas Murasawa-san doing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.50,0:10:32.23,DCMain,REIKO,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.51,0:10:34.73,DCMain,REIKO,0000,0000,0000,,I'd like to know the answer \Nto that question, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.24,0:10:38.05,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,What's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.05,0:10:39.03,DCMain,REIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Don't touch that!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.62,0:10:41.26,DCMain,REIKO,0000,0000,0000,,It belongs to Shuichi.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.26,0:10:42.57,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,What is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.79,0:10:45.99,DCMain,REIKO,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know, but it seemed important to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.99,0:10:50.08,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,That's a tuning hammer used to tune pianos.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.66,0:10:52.16,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Does that mean he...?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.23,0:10:56.96,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,In any case, gather all the \Nsuspects at the village office.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.96,0:10:58.63,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,We're going to interview them again.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.63,0:10:59.44,DCMain,POLICE,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.64,0:11:10.14,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,What is it, Conan-kun?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.49,0:11:12.94,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The suspicious person who \Nfled through the window
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.94,0:11:15.98,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,was searching the bottom \Nof the piano before they ran.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.22,0:11:19.00,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I thought there might be something here.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.16,0:11:25.87,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,What? Seriously?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.87,0:11:27.42,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,It's a secret door.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.43,0:11:33.00,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,What is this? Could it be?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.96,0:11:43.05,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Judging by the methods used,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.25,0:11:44.97,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,the three murders that have taken place
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.97,0:11:48.31,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,on this island were almost certainly \Ncommitted by the same person.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.77,0:11:50.10,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.10,0:11:52.31,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Something's not right.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.77,0:11:57.54,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Ever since I saw the code left at the second \Ncrime scene, something has seemed strange.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.12,0:11:59.18,DCMain,POLICE,0000,0000,0000,,Inspector Megure.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.92,0:12:03.01,DCMain,POLICE,0000,0000,0000,,The photos we took of the scene of \NKuroiwa's murder have been developed.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.49,0:12:04.63,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.63,0:12:06.36,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Could you lay them out over there?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.36,0:12:07.01,DCMain,POLICE,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.66,0:12:10.16,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Doctor Narumi, is Murasawa-san still unconscious?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.16,0:12:13.17,DCMain,NARUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Reiko-san is taking care of him, but he still hasn't regained consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.26,0:12:19.83,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,What's this thing shining by Kuroiwa-san's neck?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.90,0:12:23.41,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,It disappeared after the body was moved.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.88,0:12:25.17,DCMain,HIRATA,0000,0000,0000,,Um, Inspector?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.65,0:12:27.43,DCMain,HIRATA,0000,0000,0000,,Could I go buy something to drink?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.90,0:12:29.76,DCMain,HIRATA,0000,0000,0000,,I'm thirsty.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.18,0:12:31.62,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Very well.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.52,0:12:37.80,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, mister.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.28,0:12:40.28,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,You've got white powder on your sleeve.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.63,0:12:46.66,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Wow, that's a lot of foreign money.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.28,0:12:50.18,DCMain,HIRATA,0000,0000,0000,,I like foreign coins.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.18,0:12:51.56,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.29,0:12:54.00,DCMain,POLICE,0000,0000,0000,,K-Kid!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.10,0:12:59.98,DCMain,POLICE,0000,0000,0000,,I finally found the sheet \Nmusic Aso-san left behind.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.98,0:13:01.03,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Let me see that.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.03,0:13:02.17,DCMain,POLICE,0000,0000,0000,,Hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.25,0:13:05.98,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,"To my son Seiji."
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.51,0:13:12.64,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I thought Aso-san had a wife and \Ndaughter who he took with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.66,0:13:16.02,DCMain,POLICE,0000,0000,0000,,Come to think of it, he had a son, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.26,0:13:21.73,DCMain,POLICE,0000,0000,0000,,He fell terribly ill as a child and \Nwas hospitalized on the mainland.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.73,0:13:23.77,DCMain,POLICE,0000,0000,0000,,I believe his name was...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.77,0:13:25.00,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Seiji.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.50,0:13:27.28,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Could it be?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.37,0:13:39.71,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I see. So that's how it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.97,0:13:45.39,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The reason the culprit moved Kawashima-san \Nto the piano room after drowning him.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.38,0:13:49.43,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The meaning behind the music \Nleft at all three crime scenes.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.75,0:13:54.22,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,And the mystery of the code written in blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.99,0:13:58.24,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,It's definitely them. They're the culprit.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.73,0:14:01.73,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong with you?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.02,0:14:04.95,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Why'd you suddenly run \Ninto the broadcast room?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.63,0:14:10.24,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,In any case, tomorrow morning we'll \Ninterview you two and Murasawa-san,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.45,0:14:12.08,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,who's resting at the clinic.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.08,0:14:17.24,DCItalic,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Inspector, I've figured out most of what happened on this island.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.24,0:14:19.00,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Dad?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.13,0:14:23.86,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,First, the person who knocked out \NMurasawa-san in the piano room tonight
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.13,0:14:26.23,DCItalic,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,was Hirata-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.12,0:14:31.64,DCItalic,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,He suffered the injury on his left hand when he broke through the window and fled.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.17,0:14:38.46,DCItalic,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Hirata-san was using the secret door \Non the underside of the piano
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.01,0:14:40.03,DCItalic,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,to conduct drug deals with Kawashima.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.03,0:14:41.35,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,D-Drugs?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.82,0:14:44.32,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,He probably struck Murasawa-san
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.32,0:14:48.84,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,and ran because he saw him \Ncollecting the leftover drugs.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.84,0:14:52.15,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Then he got into an argument over \Nthe drugs with Kawashima, and...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.15,0:14:53.03,DCMain,HIRATA,0000,0000,0000,,N-No!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.29,0:14:57.16,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,However, Hirata-san isn't \Nconnected to the three murders.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.31,0:14:58.03,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.03,0:15:02.54,DCItalic,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,If he were the culprit, he wouldn't have \Nmoved the body into the piano room.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.85,0:15:06.31,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,After all, the drugs left in \Nthe piano could be discovered.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.55,0:15:08.06,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.06,0:15:11.41,DCItalic,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Then there's Murasawa-san, \Nwho was knocked out.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.90,0:15:13.16,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,He's the culprit?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.52,0:15:14.51,DCItalic,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}He isn't the culprit either.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.51,0:15:15.43,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.09,0:15:19.18,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,The culprit prepared a suicide note \Nto disguise his murder as a suicide,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.73,0:15:23.69,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,but they fled in such a hurry that \Nthey forgot to leave a step.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.88,0:15:26.92,DCItalic,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,It's hard to imagine someone who did \Nthat would go to the piano room.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.92,0:15:28.49,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Y-You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.69,0:15:30.74,DCItalic,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Then who killed them?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.95,0:15:33.99,DCItalic,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Direct your attention to the second case.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.69,0:15:39.80,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Kuroiwa-san was allegedly murdered only a \Nfew minutes before his body was discovered.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.57,0:15:43.79,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Recall how the code written in blood
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.39,0:15:50.09,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,didn't smear even though \NConan fell on top of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.97,0:15:53.96,DCItalic,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,However, at room temperature,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.96,0:15:56.00,DCItalic,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,it takes blood 15 to 30 minutes to dry.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.44,0:16:01.60,DCItalic,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Because there were only five \Nminutes and 30 seconds of silence
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.86,0:16:04.52,DCItalic,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,at the start of the tape that was playing,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.52,0:16:08.73,DCItalic,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,we believed the murder occurred only a few \Nminutes before the body was discovered.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.74,0:16:14.06,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,But by playing the tape from the blank B side,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.06,0:16:18.58,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,the culprit delayed the music \Nby over 30 minutes
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.36,0:16:21.75,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,using the tape player's auto-reverse feature.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.02,0:16:23.50,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Auto-reverse?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.73,0:16:26.82,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Normally, once a tape player \Nfinishes playing the A side,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.82,0:16:32.36,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,you flip over the cassette and \Nbegin playing the B side.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.36,0:16:36.45,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,But the auto-reverse feature inverts the \Ntape head to play the opposite side.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.24,0:16:39.09,DCItalic,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Take a look at the crime scene photos.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.84,0:16:44.22,DCItalic,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,There's a switch shining next to the body's neck,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.22,0:16:48.43,DCItalic,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,but in the photo taken after \Nthe body was moved, it's gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.22,0:16:53.96,DCItalic,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,It proves the culprit deactivated the \Nauto-reverse while the police weren't looking.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.96,0:16:57.66,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,But the only person who \Napproached the body then was...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.72,0:17:01.45,DCItalic,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,The only person besides the police \Nwho could approach the body
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.94,0:17:07.46,DCItalic,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,or fake the estimated time of death was\N the person who examined it, Doctor Narumi.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.99,0:17:10.96,DCItalic,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,You're the only one who could have done it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.96,0:17:12.84,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Doctor Narumi?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.84,0:17:17.39,DCItalic,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,The reason you left a few minutes of \Nsilence at the beginning on the tape
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.39,0:17:19.05,DCItalic,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,that played during the first murder
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.50,0:17:23.92,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,was to make us believe \Nthe culprit once again
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.92,0:17:27.31,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,used that same silence during the \Nsecond murder to flee the crime scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.82,0:17:31.17,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Furthermore, you drowned Kawashima-san
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.17,0:17:33.98,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,so the coroner would return to \Nthe mainland with the body,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.53,0:17:37.32,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,and so you'd be asked to examine \Nthe body during the second murder,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.69,0:17:39.82,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,allowing you to enact your trick.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.49,0:17:44.79,DCItalic,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Doctor Narumi's motive for \Nthese three murders
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.79,0:17:47.24,DCItalic,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,can be traced back to 12 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.24,0:17:48.71,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,12 years ago?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.19,0:17:54.41,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,12 years ago, the pianist Aso Keiji-san \Nburned himself to death.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.01,0:17:57.62,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,However, he was actually murdered
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.13,0:18:02.33,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,by Kawashima-san, Kuroiwa-san,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.33,0:18:03.57,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,and Nishimoto-san,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.25,0:18:07.85,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,who were killed in this case, as well as \NKameyama-san, who died two years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.10,0:18:09.98,DCMain,MURDER,0000,0000,0000,,H-He was murdered?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.45,0:18:14.63,DCItalic,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,They used Aso-san's \Ninternational performances
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.14,0:18:19.09,DCItalic,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,to purchase drugs and used the secret \Ndoor in the piano to sell them.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.77,0:18:23.95,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,However, Aso-san told them that he \Nwouldn't work with them anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.81,0:18:33.50,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,All of this is described in the sheet music \Nfound in the burnt remains of the house.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.80,0:18:40.76,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Just before his death, Aso-san wrote \Na confession to his son Seiji.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.99,0:18:42.16,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,His son?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.62,0:18:45.39,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, Seiji? Could it be?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.39,0:18:47.85,AsaiNarumi,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Asai      Narumi
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.84,0:18:48.80,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Doctor Narumi's actual name is Seiji.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.85,0:18:51.44,AsaiNarumi,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Asai          Seiji
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.34,0:18:53.26,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}He's actually Aso Keiji's son, Aso Seiji.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.44,0:18:53.65,AsaiNarumi,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(210,1)}Aso           Seiji
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.04,0:18:55.21,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,No way.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.21,0:18:58.68,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,So he did it to avenge his father?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.68,0:18:59.83,DCMain,POLICE,0000,0000,0000,,Inspector!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.20,0:19:01.80,DCMain,POLICE,0000,0000,0000,,Asai Narumi is missing.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.80,0:19:02.41,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.20,0:19:06.26,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Find him! Don't let him escape!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.26,0:19:07.40,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,He'll be there,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.91,0:19:10.04,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,where his father's piano was donated.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.88,0:19:12.65,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The Moonshade Island community center!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.55,0:19:20.51,DCMain,NARUMI,0000,0000,0000,,It's over, Dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.17,0:19:22.47,DCMain,NARUMI,0000,0000,0000,,It's all over.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.64,0:19:25.40,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,It's not over yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.68,0:19:28.31,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,You can't die.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.96,0:19:30.31,DCMain,NARUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Conan-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.81,0:19:34.31,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,It's written right here in the\Nsheet music your father left you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.53,0:19:38.32,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,"Seiji, at least you can live a decent life."
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.51,0:19:42.34,DCMain,NARUMI,0000,0000,0000,,If he'd written that,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.34,0:19:45.22,DCMain,NARUMI,0000,0000,0000,,then maybe I wouldn't have needed to do this.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.22,0:19:45.83,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.91,0:19:50.92,DCMain,NARUMI,0000,0000,0000,,I couldn't believe that my father had done that.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.53,0:19:54.71,DCMain,NARUMI,0000,0000,0000,,I couldn't believe he'd killed my mother \Nand sister before killing himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.22,0:20:00.07,DCMain,NARUMI,0000,0000,0000,,So after graduating from medical school, I \Ncame to this island in order to find the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.17,0:20:05.69,DCMain,NARUMI,0000,0000,0000,,I disguised myself as a woman doctor so people \Nwouldn't discover that I was Aso Keiji's son.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.30,0:20:11.19,DCMain,NARUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Since the reading of my name isn't written on \Nmy medical license, nobody suspected me.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.56,0:20:15.83,DCMain,NARUMI,0000,0000,0000,,I learned what happened to my father
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.83,0:20:20.18,DCMain,NARUMI,0000,0000,0000,,when the previous mayor Kameyama \Ntold me to meet him here in this room.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.73,0:20:24.41,DCMain,NARUMI,0000,0000,0000,,When he learned that I was Aso Keiji's son,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.41,0:20:27.24,DCMain,NARUMI,0000,0000,0000,,he suddenly became frightened \Nand told me everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.49,0:20:32.50,DCMain,NARUMI,0000,0000,0000,,About the drugs, the code, \Nand my father's murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.22,0:20:36.35,DCMain,NARUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Once he finished talking, he \Nwas suddenly wracked with pain.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.75,0:20:40.37,DCMain,NARUMI,0000,0000,0000,,He died of a heart attack.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.43,0:20:45.76,DCMain,NARUMI,0000,0000,0000,,That's when I came up with these murders...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.40,0:20:52.64,DCMain,NARUMI,0000,0000,0000,,while playing the "Moonlight Sonata" my \Nfather loved next to his body as a requiem.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.39,0:20:58.69,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,In any case, let's get out of here, Seiji-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.14,0:21:00.53,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,There's still time.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.82,0:21:02.36,DCMain,NARUMI,0000,0000,0000,,It's too late.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.56,0:21:03.26,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.69,0:21:07.07,DCMain,NARUMI,0000,0000,0000,,My hands are like theirs now.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.17,0:21:10.08,DCMain,NARUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Covered in blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.60,0:21:11.83,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Seiji-san...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.34,0:21:17.22,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Conan-kun?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.22,0:21:18.13,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.13,0:21:19.28,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Don't!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.84,0:21:21.15,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Let go!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.97,0:21:24.78,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,What's that sound?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.61,0:21:26.88,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,A code.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.34,0:21:32.23,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,He's playing the piano amidst those flames.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.67,0:22:46.17,Thanks,,0000,0000,0000,,Special Thanks\NTo everyone who loves Conan
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.30,0:23:03.40,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The community center continued to burn until \Nmorning, when it finally burnt down completely.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.91,0:23:10.64,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Apparently Murasawa-san missed the pianist \NAso Keiji and occasionally tuned that piano.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.02,0:23:14.04,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,It's what he was doing the night he was struck.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.54,0:23:17.42,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.00,0:23:21.81,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder why Doctor Narumi \Nsent Dad that letter.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.69,0:23:27.88,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,He probably wanted someone to stop \Nhim from murdering those people.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.27,0:23:33.93,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, what was the code Doctor Narumi played?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.36,0:23:36.31,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I forgot already.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.31,0:23:39.06,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,I can tell by the look on your \Nface that you haven't.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.48,0:23:44.70,Thank you,RIGHT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(710,1620)}Thank you,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.52,0:23:41.28,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, tell me.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.64,0:23:44.70,littledetective,LEFT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(710,1620)}little detective.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.03,0:23:43.22,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,I'll tickle you.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.22,0:23:44.72,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Stop!
